We have [Closeds](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Sets/Closeds.html#TopologicalSpace.Closeds) and similarly for Clopens. Should we have a definition for IrreducibleCloseds as well? If so please also change the line [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8932a3d688d2bbf500429c4c888de4181086aad5/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/PrimeSpectrum/Basic.lean#L960-L964)
I think yes. `irreducibleComponents_eq_maximals_closed` also mentions this.

> So does `vanishingIdeal_isClosed_isIrreducible` (this time in the other order). This proof is only used once in mathlib, in the proof of `vanishingIdeal_irreducibleComponents` (which is now worse than it was). To avoid this regression probably `vanishingIdeal_isClosed_isIrreducible` should be renamed `vanishingIdeal_isIrreducibleClosed` and fixed up to use this new concept.

I have made changes according to your advice. Consequently, the names of some results have been changed.
I have added a structure `IrreducibleCloseds` and refactored some declarations to use it.
Why not add some TODOs? For example Krull dimension of Spec(R) is Krull dimension of R, for R a commutative ring (do we have Krull dimension of a commutative ring?)
I added the TODO comment. That result is proven in #6277, which is too big, but @FMLJohn  is working on splitting it into smaller PRs.

Should we define `IrreducibleCloseds` as a subtype and set up an order on `IrreducibleCloseds` and define `topologicalKrullDim` as `krullDim( irreducibleCloseds T)`? Similarly in other places as well.

Whether or not we do this, we have `IsIrreducible` and `IsClosed` so I don't see any harm in `IsIrreducibleClosed` for now. @erdOne do you have an opinion on this? If we're happy with the definition as it is, this is probably ready to go now. But if we want to change, probably now is a good time to do it.
I added that definition.
Does this not follow from `SetLike` via typeclass inference?
I think you should just replace `irreducibleSetEquivPoints`.

